name: Colombia Aponte Village Honey
video: Lance Hedrick: was funny & very sincere & genuine
overall: Warm, cozy, very good red honey just not my fave. 8/10

name: Ethiopia Shakiso Female-Produced Natural
video: Loud & Casual just about the producer
overall: Coffee great. [The gf] liked it. FLoral but chill about it. Fruity, light, but very approachable.

name: Kenya Gakuyu-ini AA
video: X
overall: Kind of boring, but tasty...Very washed, paltable...6/10

name: Uganda Long Miles Lunar Station
video: Earnest. "Sometimes you get a natural that's like "Bwoop!""
overall: Super soft mouthfeel. Sweet, kind of delicate. 8/10

name: Framily
video: Video had US Cycling team. Very cute
overall: Extremely good as it cools. Perfect washed Ethiopia 10/10

name: Costa Rica Las Lajas Natural
video: Morgan Eckroth
smell: Deeply sweet chocolate + rich fruity like a fudge with cranberries
overall: Med-light body juicy fruity but w/ solid chocolate/grounded floor. Sides of tongue...

name: Uganda Kamogo Station
video: World Barista 2025 Champion Jack Simpson
smell: Floral & Spicy, but not overwhelming. Very Pleasant
overall: Comfy. Stonefruit bottom & rounded + tasty. Chocolate finish...maybe nut.

name: Ethiopia Hambela Alaka Natural
video: Jon Lampley tiktok style video. Good editing and very fast.
smell: Deep chocolate that resolves to fruit.
overall: Perfect comfy Ethiopia natural. Fruit forward & deep w/o being crazy. 10/10

name: El Salvador Santa Rosa
video: Jorge Raul Rivera -> owner of coffee
overall: Very OK. Maybe a bad brew. Def good, just nothing special. A classy Med. roast 5/10

name: Guatemala El Socorro Purpuracca
video: Jerry Truong USA 2025 Barista Champion
overall: It's the standard good "wahsed." That kind of default apple flavor. 4/10

name: Colombia Edward Sandoval Chiroso
video: Zedd. Very "here are my espresso accessories"
overall: Light,j floral, very fruity but rounded out by the wash. 9/10

name: Mexico Mazateca Mujeres
video: Sam spillman - Cafe Mire(?). Great coffee prep video explanation of varietals
overall: It's a really good central American washed coffee but w/ a kind of fermented, sweet sting changing it for the better. Juicy grapefruit. 8/10

name: Krampus
video: Goofy "Krampus" spooky forest horror movie
overall: Tobacco first, but not offensive. A little smoky. Not a daily driver but interesting. 7/10

name: El Salvador Santa Rosa Honey
video: Jose Raul Rivera (producer). Honest & simple
smell: Very light smell. Delicate "coffee" scent. Pleasant.
overall: Rose, syrupy fruit but not heavy at all.

name: Ethiopia Lalesa Ephtah Site Slow Dry Natural
video: Dakota Graff. Chill explanation about the coffee & women-owned collective.
smell: Very very deep sweetness. Almost buttery sweet (not saccharine)
overall: Deep sweetness. Almost peanut butter aftertaste. Super comfy & tasty. 10/10

name: Panama Hacienda Barbara Catuai Natural
video: Cole Torode in Panama. Sourcer.
smell: Not strong, but very deeply natural & fruity.
overall: Developed fruit roast. No spice, but "chocolate & compote" for sure.

name: Kenya Kamunyaka AA
video: Peter Mbature. Cool earnest video about the coffee.
overall: Top-notch comfy fruit. Mango for sure. 9/10

name: Ethiopia Bombe Natural
video: Kay Cheon - terrible audio (cutting off) but understandable. He's on a mountain pouring this
overall: explosive sweetness, rounded in that deep natural way 9/10

name: Colombia John Diaz Pink Bourbon
video: Pedro Eschavarria -> works w/ producers. Good simple video about coffee & prep.
overall: Classic washed natural but w/ citrus finish. Not super floral, but more than berry 9/10

name: Honduras Sagastume Family Natural
video: Benjamin Paz (Honduras producer). Demonstration + info about the coffee
overall: Not great cuz I tried it in the new OXO rapid brewer for the first time

name: Colombia Jairo Arcila Lychee
video: Juan Camilio Zuluaga. Cool vibes from this guy. I see his company goat logo in the Demo + explanation
smell: Said "oh my god" aloud cuz so fruity. Kinda grapey or apple. Apricot.
overall: INSANELY cool. Rich & fruity! Like candy apple but not fermented 10/10

name: Kenya Elshadai Coffee Estate Natural
video: Morgan Eckroth again. Fine. She seems to really like this one.
smell: Raisins, a malty sugar. Really cool.
overall: Malty, a little fermented. A chill, not in-your-face candy flavor 9/10

name: Guatemala El Socorro Maracaturra
video: Akie Bermiss. Passionate about light roasts. Brewred & talked about the roasts "playfulness"
smell: Perfect light roast smell. Nothing crazy
overall: Full body, juicy fruit. Rounded chocolate

name: Panama Hacienda Esmeralda Gesha
video: Rachel Peterson. Talking about creating coffee w/ simplicity. Using hoop.
overall: Lemon, light stone fruit finish
